Rating: 4
Because of the prior concerns of this needing a little spark, I sauteed about 1/4 lb of cubed pancetta before the leeks and this came out very tasty (I served the nuts on the side) and will definitely make it again for guests.

Rating: 3
This is an easy and tasty recipe. I did the following to add flavor: Saute the garlic in the oil prior to adding the leeks until transparent. Gives more flavor. Also added more lemon peel. Important to use the Pecorino Romano cheese.

Rating: 2
This was ok, I tend to like powerful flavors and this was lacking. I think 2x the lemon zest would help, I also added some crushed red pepper and anise seed the second day to try and spice it up.

Rating: 2
This was pretty good. After eating it however I'm pretty sure that they meant for you to mince or chop the garlic and that is omitted in the instructions. It just says "4 cloves peeled" with nothing about chopping. I did just that and ate one of the whole cloves which was pretty awful.